            "body": "Interestingly, it works as expected if the Lua function returns any expandable item between `%1*` and `%*`, as opposed to just the \"MyFunc\" text.\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:lua MyFunc = function() return \"%1*MyFunc%t%*\" end\r\n```\r\n```vim\r\n:set statusline=--%(x%{%v:lua.MyFunc()%}x%)--\r\n```\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3299086/92f2a32c-50fb-4233-a9df-52bc290d8b86)",
